data.name: richTextBox2.Text
data.value:
============================= Connect ================================ : 'Connect' section is for RS232 connection between laser module and Optilab GUI software
How to connect your device ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
a) Please choose your TWL comport from drop down menu. b) Click 'Connect' button and you will be connected to your laser module
Buttons ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Close : This button will close connection between laser module and software
- Exit : This button close both connection between laser module & software and application
=========================== Device Information ========================= : 'Device Information' section will be activated if RS232 connection has been successfully completed. It read/display information from laser.
Data ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Serial Connection : It shows whether RS232 connection is successful or not.
- Power Capability : It shows the range of laser's power in 'dBm'.
- Frequency Range : It shows the range of laser's frequency in 'THz'. It will display up to 4 decimal places if possible.
- Wavelength Range : It shows the range of laser's wavelength in 'nm'. It will display up to 4 decimal places if possible.
- Fine Tune Frequency Range : It shows the range of laser's fine tune frequency, 'MHz' tuning capability.
- Maximum Buad Rate : It shows current buad rate of RS232 connection.

data.name: richTextBox3.Text
data.value:
============================== Setting ================================ : 'Setting' is where you can set your power & wavelength of laser.
Power Setting -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
a) You can type power level in 'dBm' and click 'Set' button. b) When number typed is bigger or smaller than its capability, pop-up message will shows up. Please refer to 'General' tab to find out laser's power capability.
Wavelength Setting -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Frequency Setting
1) You can type frequency in 'THz' and click 'Set' button. 2) You can tune your frequency up to 'MHz' part (depends on laser, please refer to your 'Fine Tune Frequency Range'), Which means up to 6 decimal places (i.e. 192.123456) 3) When number typed is bigger or smaller than its capability, pop-up message will shows up. Please refer to 'General' tab to find out frequency range.
- Wavelength Setting
1) You can type wavelength in 'nm' and click 'Set' button. 2) You can tune your frequency up to 'MHz' part (depends on laser, please refer to your 'Fine Tune Frequency Range'), Which means up to 4 decimal places (i.e. 1550.2345) 3) When number typed is bigger or smaller than its capability, pop-up message will shows up. Please refer to 'General' tab to find out frequency range.
- Channel(ITU-Grid) Setting
1) You need to choose grid spacing from dropbox menu ('50G' or '100G'). Then type integer and click 'Set' button (Please refer to ITU-Grid table on 'ITU-Grid' tab under 'Help') 2) Channel setting does not take MHz tune. 3) When set channel is bigger or smaller than its capability, pop-up message will shows up. Please refer to 'General' tab & 'ITU-Grid' table to find out frequency range.
Buttons ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Enable : This button enable/disable laser
- Save as Default : After setting laser power & frequency, you can save setting with this button. Upon power on or hard reset, the module loads these configuration settings
============================Device Status============================ : 'Device Status' indicate current values for power, frequency, wavelength and temperature of laser
Data ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Power : It shows current power level in 'dBm'
- Frequency : It shows current frequency of laser in 'THz'. It will display up to 4 decimal places if possible (But setting frequency up to 6 decimal places is available).
- Wavelength : It shows current wavelength of laser in 'nm'. It will display up to 4 decimal places if possible.
- Temperature : It shows current temperature of laser in 'Celsius'
Buttons ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Status Update : This button update current values of laser.
- Real Time : This button enable/disable real-time reading from laser module.
- Save Data : This button will export laser module reading in excel file.
============================== Option ================================ : 'Option' provide optional functions to user but not available for every laser module. Please contact optilab for eligible laser module.
Low Noise Mode ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
: This mode provide low noise mode for laser module
Dither -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) You can type amount of frequency value you want to dither to laser in 'GHz'. Then click 'Set' button. 2) Click 'ON' button to enable/disable

data.value:
============================= How to Scan =============================
1. Choose Serial Number from dropbox menu : It is important to choose right 'Serial Number'. If different, scan function will not work properly and may damage laser.
2. Determine range of scanning. : User can either check 'Entire Range Scan' for scanning from first to last frequency of laser or manually type 'Start' and 'Stop' frequency. When choose manually, available range will show up on top of box
3. Determine sweep range (GHz) : It is recommended to use a 100GHz sweep range as this optimizes the speed of the sweep (because the sweeps get slower at larger deviations and because more jumps are required with shorter sweeps).
4. Choose Target Power (dBm) : As of 'Optilab TWL GUI v1.0' , available target power is only 10dBm.
5. Click Scan button : When every setting is done, click 'Scan' button and TWL module will start scanning.
6. 'Stop' Button : While TWL module is scanning, click 'Stop' if you want to cancel your scanning. Otherwise, it will automatically stop after scanning selected range.
============================ Status Display =============================
1. Current Center Frequency : 'Current Center Frequency' shows center frequency of current sweep, size defined by 'Sweep Range'
2. Status Window : Status window will display informtation to user such as start, stop or cancel of scanning.
3. Clear button : Clear button will clear the display of status window.
